Guns should protect people rather than kill them. Schools and public places should be safe. The younger generations of Americans should live without fear of gun violence. But in reality, American people are continuously getting murdered, not just by guns, but by political divide and stalemate, institutional failures and chronic diseases in American society. How many more bullets does America have to take before someone finally pulls the trigger of change? Here’s “America at Gunpoint,” a CGTN 30-minute special on gun violence - from the prevalence of young shooters and hate crimes to the stalemate on the gun debate in the U.S.